使用这个模板帮我写一份申请Joint PhD的Personal Statement的模板，不要用这个表和小标题

下面给你一个**基于你提供的 IEEEtran 模板风格**（10pt、onecolumn、1.5 倍行距、常用宏包等）的 **Joint PhD 申请 Personal Statement（个人陈述）LaTeX 模板**。我已按你的要求：**不使用表格**、**不使用“小标题/分节标题”（如 \section、\subsection）**；改为用加粗行内引导语与自然段组织结构。你只需替换其中的占位内容即可。

```latex
\documentclass[10pt,journal,onecolumn,final]{IEEEtran}

% ---------- Packages (keep close to your style) ----------
\usepackage{amssymb}
\usepackage{amsmath}
\usepackage{cite}

\ifCLASSINFOpdf
\usepackage[pdftex]{graphicx}
\graphicspath{{../pdf/}{../jpeg/}}
\DeclareGraphicsExtensions{.pdf,.jpeg,.png}
\else
\fi

\usepackage{url}
\usepackage{hyperref}
\usepackage[dvipsnames]{xcolor}
\usepackage{booktabs}
\usepackage{setspace}
\usepackage{lmodern}
\setstretch{1.5}

% ---------- Personal info macros ----------
\newcommand{\ApplicantName}{YOUR NAME}
\newcommand{\Email}{your.email@domain.com}
\newcommand{\Phone}{+86-XXX-XXXX-XXXX}
\newcommand{\CurrentAffiliation}{Shanghai Jiao Tong University}
\newcommand{\TargetProgram}{Joint PhD Program in XXX}
\newcommand{\TargetSchool}{University A \& University B}
\newcommand{\AdvisorA}{Prof.~A (University A)}
\newcommand{\AdvisorB}{Prof.~B (University B)}
\newcommand{\ResearchArea}{Computer Vision / Machine Learning / (edit)}

\begin{document}

\clearpage
\noindent
{\LARGE\bfseries Personal Statement}\\[8pt]

\noindent
{\large\bfseries \ApplicantName}\\
\noindent
{\normalsize
\CurrentAffiliation \hfill \Email \\
\Phone \hfill Application: \TargetProgram, \TargetSchool
}\\[10pt]

\noindent
I am applying for the \textbf{\TargetProgram} at \textbf{\TargetSchool}. My research interest lies in \textbf{\ResearchArea}, with a particular focus on \textbf{(one-sentence focus, e.g., robust representation learning, 3D vision, generative modeling, multimodal learning)}. My long-term goal is to become a researcher who develops principled and deployable methods that address real-world constraints such as \textbf{data scarcity, distribution shift, efficiency, safety, or interpretability}. Through rigorous training and cross-institution collaboration in a Joint PhD setting, I aim to advance both the theoretical understanding and practical impact of \textbf{(your topic)}.

\noindent
\textbf{Motivation and academic preparation.}
My interest in \textbf{(your field)} began when I \textbf{(brief origin story: a course, a project, an internship, a research exposure)}. During my undergraduate/graduate study at \textbf{(institution)}, I built a solid foundation in \textbf{(core courses: linear algebra, probability, optimization, ML, CV, etc.)} and strengthened my research skills through \textbf{(reading groups, labs, independent projects)}. These experiences trained me to formulate problems, implement reproducible pipelines, and communicate results clearly.

\noindent
\textbf{Research experience and outcomes.}
My most important research experience is \textbf{(Project/Thesis title)} in which I studied \textbf{(problem statement)}. The key challenge was \textbf{(e.g., noisy labels, limited annotations, domain shift, long-tailed data)}. I addressed it by \textbf{(your approach: model design, algorithm, theoretical insight)}. Concretely, I \textbf{(method details at a high level)} and conducted experiments on \textbf{(datasets/benchmarks)}. The results showed \textbf{(quantitative improvement or qualitative finding)}, and the work led to \textbf{(preprint/submission/publication/open-source)}.
If applicable, I also learned to collaborate efficiently by \textbf{(code review, experiment tracking, ablation studies, documentation)}, ensuring that the conclusions are robust and repeatable.

\noindent
In addition, I worked on \textbf{(Project 2 / internship)} where I focused on \textbf{(another angle: systems, deployment, efficiency, product constraints)}. This experience made me aware of the gap between academic benchmarks and real-world requirements. I learned to balance \textbf{performance, computational cost, and reliability} by \textbf{(profiling, pruning, distillation, data-centric iterations, evaluation under shift)}. These skills will be directly useful for research in a Joint PhD program that values both depth and breadth.

\noindent
\textbf{Why a Joint PhD and why \TargetSchool.}
I am particularly attracted to a Joint PhD structure because it provides \textbf{(1--2 concrete reasons: complementary strengths of two labs, access to unique resources, cross-cultural research environment, joint supervision)}. I am interested in working with \textbf{\AdvisorA} because \textbf{(connect their work to your interest; cite 1-2 topics/papers/lines of work)}. I am also eager to learn from \textbf{\AdvisorB} whose research on \textbf{(topic)} aligns with my goal of \textbf{(goal)}. I believe the combination of these two research environments will allow me to pursue ambitious questions such as \textbf{(2--3 specific research questions)} while maintaining strong methodological rigor and practical relevance.

\noindent
\textbf{Proposed research direction.}
In the Joint PhD, I plan to investigate \textbf{(your main direction)}. One possible starting point is \textbf{(direction A)}, where I aim to \textbf{(goal)} by exploring \textbf{(methods)}. Another direction is \textbf{(direction B)}, focusing on \textbf{(goal)} under constraints such as \textbf{(data/compute/robustness)}. In terms of methodology, I intend to combine \textbf{(e.g., representation learning + causal/uncertainty/optimization; or multimodal + diffusion; or theory + systems)} and validate ideas with \textbf{(benchmarks + real data + ablations)}. I also value open and reproducible research, and I plan to maintain well-documented code, rigorous evaluation protocols, and clear reporting of limitations.

\noindent
\textbf{Strengths, values, and fit.}
I consider my strengths to be \textbf{(e.g., strong implementation, careful experimentation, mathematical maturity, writing)}. I enjoy iterative research cycles: understanding prior work, building baselines, diagnosing failure modes, and designing targeted improvements. I also value teamwork and integrity; I maintain transparent experiment logs and report negative results when necessary. These habits help me contribute reliably to collaborative projects across institutions, which is essential for a Joint PhD.

\noindent
\textbf{Career plan.}
After completing the Joint PhD, I hope to pursue a career in \textbf{(academia / industrial research / both)}, working on \textbf{(your long-term problems)} and collaborating internationally. In the long run, I aim to build research that is not only publishable but also \textbf{reproducible, trustworthy, and impactful}.

\noindent
Thank you for considering my application. I would be honored to contribute to the research community at \textbf{\TargetSchool} and to grow under the joint supervision of \textbf{\AdvisorA} and \textbf{\AdvisorB}.\\[12pt]

\noindent
{\normalsize
Sincerely,\\
\ApplicantName
}

\end{document}
```

